  "prompt": "My girlfriend and I took a break. About two months later she told me she made out with her ex during our break. What do I do?",
  "response": "This is a tough situation. Here are some potential steps to consider:\n\n1. Process your emotions\n- Take time to understand how you feel\n- Are you hurt, angry, betrayed, or indifferent?\n\n2. Have an honest conversation with her\n- Discuss the details of what happened\n- Understand the context of your break and her actions\n- Express your feelings openly and calmly\n\n3. Reflect on your relationship\n- Consider whether you can truly move past this\n- Evaluate the trust in your relationship\n- Think about whether this is a deal-breaker for you\n\n4. Consider your options\n- Reconcile and work through the issue\n- End the relationship\n- Take more time to think about it\n\n5. If you decide to continue the relationship\n- Set clear boundaries\n- Rebuild trust gradually\n- Be prepared to work on communication\n\n6. Consider seeking advice from:\n- Trusted friends\n- Family members\n- A relationship counselor\n\nRemember, there's no universal \"right\" answer. The best decision depends on your specific situation, feelings, and relationship dynamics.\n\nUltimately, trust your feelings and do what's best for your emotional well-being.",
